So basically, anything that uses boringssl will likely be broken on s390x.
In fact, the only part of TensorFlow that uses boringssl is the core/platform/cloud:oauth_client target.
@Nayana-ibm since that target is not going to work anyway, could you look into removing this patch, and simply disabling the oauth support on big endian instead?

